# OPEN_QUESTIONS.md

## Purpose

Track design-stage open questions for {{ project.name }}.

This optional template records unresolved decisions without copying raw source content, sensitive values, or downstream-specific implementation details.

## Scope

- Owner-review source decisions.
- Design risks.
- Deferred decisions.
- P2/P3 boundary questions.
- Follow-up approvals.

## Source Use

Open questions may refer to source row identifiers only. Owner-review source rows must not be summarized beyond approved category-level metadata until the owner accepts, revises, or defers them. Excluded source rows must remain outside repository and target content.

| question_id | source row | decision state | question | owner action needed |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Q-001 | SRC-### | PENDING | TBD | accept/revise/defer |

## Prohibited Content

- Raw source excerpts.
- Sensitive requirement text.
- Private notes that reveal source content.
- Runtime implementation details.
- C# source, solution, project, XAML, build assets, scripts, or binaries.
- PLC/device code.
- Live target write support or external mutation.
- GitHub Actions or cloud CI.
- IP, port, tag value, live parameter, secret, private input, live config, credential, account, or equipment detail.

## Approval Boundary

Questions recorded here do not approve implementation, source expansion, profile creation, example creation, render integration, gate implementation, or live system access.

## Review Checklist

- Each question is generalized.
- Source references use row identifiers only.
- Owner-review rows are not used beyond allowed metadata.
- Excluded source rows remain outside repository and target content.
- Deferred decisions are clearly marked.
- Prohibited content is absent.
- Next approval need is explicit.
